-- Continental AG to Sell More Bonds Than Anticipated, Handelsblatt Reports
-- Andreas Cremer
-- 2010-06-15T05:11:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/continental-ag-to-sell-more-bonds-than-anticipated-handelsblatt-reports.html

          
          
             Continental AG  wants to sell more
bonds than planned to help repay debt,  Handelsblatt  said, citing
Chief Financial Officer  Wolfgang Schaefer .  
 The Hanover, Germany-based auto-parts maker plans to sell
as much as 4 billion euros ($4.9 billion) of bonds, including a
planned sale of between 1.5 billion and 2 billion euros in high-
yield notes, the newspaper said, citing the CFO.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
